{
  "texts": [
    "Though a full discussion of the SEC's reasons for considering certain cryptocurrencies as securities is outside of the scope of this paper, we give a brief overview.",
    "For a full consideration thereof, see Moffett (2022).",
    "The SEC and the U.S. federal courts have traditionally based their analysis as to whether a cryptocurrency constitutes a security on SEC v. W.J.",
    "(now colloquially referred to as the \"Howey test\").",
    "In this Supreme Court case, an investment contract needed to meet the following criteria: it had to be \"(1) an investment of money, (2) in a common enterprise, (3) with the expectation of profits, (4) to be derived from the entrepreneurial or managerial efforts of others\" (Moffett 2022)."
  ]
}